title: Leading goal scorers of French Ligue 1
text: Added on October 3, 2015 NewsWire Leading goal scorers of French Ligue 1 Paris, Oct 4 (IANS) The following are the leading goal scorers of French Ligue 1 after matches played on Saturday, according to Xinhua news agency. 6 – Edinson Cavani (Paris Saint-Germain), Hatem Ben Arfa (Nice) 5 – Martin Braithwaite (Toulouse), Michy Batshuayi (Marseille) 4 – Wahbi Khazri (Bordeaux), Valere Germain (Nice), Giovanni Sio (Rennes), Nabil Fekir (Lyon) 3 – Romain Alessandrini (Marseille), Jordan Siebatcheu (Reims), Thomas Lemar (Monaco), Loic Perrin (Saint-Etienne), Nicolas Benezet (Guingamp), Sloan Privat (Guingamp), Claudio Beauvue (Lyon), Benjamin Moukandjo (Lorient), Sofiane Boufal (Lille), Thomas Mangani (Angers) 2 – Angel Di Maria (Paris Saint-Germain), Zlatan Ibrahimovic (Paris Saint-Germain), Alassane Plea (Nice), Blaise Matuidi (Paris Saint-Germain), Nicolas De Preville (Reims), Paul-Georges Ntep (Rennes), Ronny Rodelin (Caen), Majeed Waris (Lorient), Julian Palmieri (Bastia), Gael Danic (Bastia), Romain Hamouma (Saint-Etienne), Sebastien Squillaci (Bastia), Jaroslav Plasil (Bordeaux), Benjamin Jeannot (Lorient), Bernardo Silva (Monaco), Henri Saivet (Bordeaux), Andy Delort (Caen), Floyd Ayite (Bastia), Younousse Sankhare (Guingamp), Cheikh Ndoye (Angers), Jonas Martin (Montpellier), Fabinho (Monaco), Alexandre Lacazette (Lyon).
